Transitivity	Valence			Example
-------------------------------------------------
intrans: 	ga			warau
intransarg2: 	to (opt)		miataru
v1: 		ga-wo (opt)		utsu
v1a: 		ga-wo (obl)		kudasaru (only)
v2: 		ga-ni (opt)		ataru
v2a: 		ga-{ni or to} (obl)	naru (only)
v3: 		ga-to (obl)		kataru
v4: 		ga-wo (opt) -ni (opt)	ditransitive
v5: 		ga-to (opt)		tsukiau, karamu
v5a: 		ga-to (obl)		oshieru, etc (only)
v6: 		ga- {ni or to} (opt)	meguriau
v7: 		ga-wo (opt) - to (obl)	omou (commented out)
v8: 		ga-noun argument (obl)	wasureru
mental: 	ga- {ga or wo}(opt)	wakaru
aru: 		aru
cop: 		cop
cop-id: 	cop-id

Obligatory arguments: it is not allowed to have zero pronouns for them.
Additionally, they may not scramble.

Mental also seems to allow "ni"

